Thanksgiving.

244
00:12:06.416 --> 00:12:08.791
Oh. right. Sorry. Tuck.

245
00:12:08.875 --> 00:12:11.583
Hannah and I are going to my dad's
place in Boston. Can't make it.

246
00:12:11.666 --> 00:12:13.833
What? No.

247
00:12:14.375 --> 00:12:15.458
Okay.

248
00:12:15.541 --> 00:12:18.375
No problem. No problem.
Dean. you can handle all his stuff. okay?

249
00:12:18.458 --> 00:12:21.458
No. I would be all over that.
but I am road-tripping

250
00:12:21.541 --> 00:12:24.041
-down to New York tomorrow with Bella.
-Oh. no. dude.

251
00:12:24.125 --> 00:12:26.375
-No. no. no. no. no. no. no.
-Blackout Wednesday. dude.

252
00:12:26.458 --> 00:12:30.000
Drinksgiving? Why would I be drunk here
when I could be drunk there?

253
00:12:30.083 --> 00:12:32.250
Sorry. bro. See you next year.

254
00:12:33.250 --> 00:12:35.833
So. the friends
are abandoning Friendsgiving.

255
00:12:35.916 --> 00:12:37.083
Who needs them?

256
00:12:37.166 --> 00:12:39.916
Jules and I are here. it's gonna be
the perfect fucking Thanksgiving.

257
00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:41.000
What do you need?

258
00:12:41.916 --> 00:12:43.541
I'll send you my to-do list.

259
00:12:44.916 --> 00:12:46.083
[phone chimes]

260
00:12:51.250 --> 00:12:52.958
-[Logan] Damn.
-[Tucker] I know.

261
00:12:53.041 --> 00:12:54.166
It's glorious.

262
00:12:59.875 --> 00:13:02.875
I'm so depressed you're not coming
to Brooklyn with me this year.

263
00:13:02.958 --> 00:13:05.208
Me. too.
But I want to be there for Garrett.

264
00:13:05.291 --> 00:13:07.583
As much as I love
watching Aunt Kathy get drunk

265
00:13:07.666 --> 00:13:09.541
and busting out her old cheer routine.

266
00:13:09.625 --> 00:13:12.166
-God. old gal's still got the splits.
-[laughs]

267
00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:14.750
It's your first Thanksgiving without Sean.
How are you doing?

268
00:13:14.833 --> 00:13:17.000
Honestly. I am loving my single life.

269
00:13:17.083 --> 00:13:20.208
I'm Yasmina in season two
of <i>Al Nisa Alashba</i>.

270
00:13:20.958 --> 00:13:24.041
Doesn't she fall into a coma
for most of that season?

271
00:13:24.125 --> 00:13:26.958
Yes. but before that.
she is single and thriving.

272
00:13:27.041 --> 00:13:28.000
As am I.

273
00:13:28.083 --> 00:13:32.250
Just not getting tied down.
focusing on myself and my acting.

274
00:13:32.333 --> 00:13:34.500
-That's it.
-Well. I am proud of you.

275
00:13:34.583 --> 00:13:35.916
Well. you. too.

276
00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:39.500
Meeting Garrett's dad.
being a good girlfriend and shit.

277
00:13:39.583 --> 00:13:41.750
-[both laugh]
-You nervous?

278
00:13:41.833 --> 00:13:42.875
Uh. no.

279
00:13:44.291 --> 00:13:45.791
I mean. he's famous. right?

280
00:13:46.333 --> 00:13:49.833
Yeah. yeah. okay. I'm a little nervous.
but not because he's famous.

281
00:13:49.916 --> 00:13:51.708
Just... I don't know.

282
00:13:51.791 --> 00:13:55.000
The way Garrett talks about him.
he seems like really intense.

283
00:13:55.083 --> 00:13:57.708
Yeah. I've seen him at games.
Does the man ever smile?

284
00:13:57.791 --> 00:13:59.291
I don't think so.

285
00:13:59.375 --> 00:14:00.541
Well. don't stress.

286
00:14:00.625 --> 00:14:02.291
It's not about him liking you.

287
00:14:02.375 --> 00:14:03.833
It's about Garrett.

288
00:14:03.916 --> 00:14:05.416
And he already likes you.

289
00:14:06.291 --> 00:14:10.000
Yeah. I just think it's really important
to Garrett that this goes well.

290
00:14:10.083 --> 00:14:12.416
That's what relationships are for.
honey bun.

291
00:14:12.500 --> 00:14:13.666
Supporting each other.

292
00:14:13.750 --> 00:14:15.750
Helping each other grow as people.

293
00:14:16.833 --> 00:14:19.041
It can't all be about sex and fun.

294
00:14:19.125 --> 00:14:20.583
[cell phone vibrates]

295
00:14:20.666 --> 00:14:22.916
Oh. shit. The bus is almost here.
Gotta go.

296
00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:25.166
Well. no. Garrett can just drive you.

297
00:14:25.250 --> 00:14:26.458
No. it's fine. I love a bus.

298
00:14:26.541 --> 00:14:27.875
You hate a bus.

299
00:14:27.958 --> 00:14:28.875
It's fine.

300
00:14:28.958 --> 00:14:30.958
I love you. Happy Thanksgiving.

301
00:14:31.041 --> 00:14:34.166
Love you. [laughs]

302
00:14:51.041 --> 00:14:53.500
-[Tucker] 425 for how long?
-[Gail on phone] <i>Thirty minutes.</i>

303
00:14:53.583 --> 00:14:56.166
<i>Use that time to prep the turkey</i>
<i>before it has to go in.</i>

304
00:14:56.250 --> 00:14:58.291
<i>-And don't forget to--</i>
-Pat-dry the bird.

305
00:14:58.375 --> 00:15:00.750
I know. I know. Can't be wet.

306
00:15:00.833 --> 00:15:03.958
<i>Unless you want a crispy turkey</i>
<i>and no eyebrows like Uncle Pete.</i>

307
00:15:04.041 --> 00:15:07.791
<i>And don't skimp on the marshmallows</i>
<i>for the sweet potato casserole.</i>

308
00:15:07.875 --> 00:15:09.583
Ooh. slivers. dude.

309
00:15:09.666 --> 00:15:11.458
Dude. slivers.

310
00:15:11.541 --> 00:15:12.416
Just... easy.

311
00:15:12.500 --> 00:15:13.583
-Yes. chef.
-There you go.

312
00:15:14.250 --> 00:15:17.500
<i>Just remember to drop the turkey in</i>
<i>exactly one hour</i>

313
00:15:17.583 --> 00:15:18.791
<i>before your sides are ready.</i>

314
00:15:18.875 --> 00:15:20.208
One hour. Got it.

315
00:15:20.291 --> 00:15:22.458
<i>First Thanksgiving</i>
<i>you're cooking all on your own.</i>

316
00:15:22.541 --> 00:15:24.083
It's weird doing all this without you.

317
00:15:24.166 --> 00:15:25.250
<i>Miss you. too. JT.</i>

318
00:15:25.333 --> 00:15:26.666
<i>But I'm right there with you.</i>

319
00:15:26.750 --> 00:15:30.666
<i>I can practically smell</i>
<i>the sweat and testosterone.</i>

320
00:15:30.750 --> 00:15:32.166
-[laughs]
-Fair.

321
00:15:32.250 --> 00:15:34.250
Just don't want to screw anything up.

322
00:15:34.333 --> 00:15:36.625
-It has to be perfect.
<i>-No such thing.</i>

323
00:15:36.708 --> 00:15:37.791
<i>It's not the food.</i>

324
00:15:37.875 --> 00:15:40.291
<i>It's the comfort and love</i>
<i>that make the food.</i>

325
00:15:40.375 --> 00:15:42.000
Did you just quote the Barefoot Contessa?

326
00:15:42.083 --> 00:15:44.916
<i>Or did she quote me?</i>
<i>No way of knowing. is there?</i>

327
00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:46.083
[laughs]

328
00:15:46.166 --> 00:15:47.375
Gravy. gotta go.

329
00:15:47.458 --> 00:15:48.666
<i>Love you. baby.</i>

330
00:15:52.291 --> 00:15:55.583
Perfect. Yes. Yes.

331
00:15:58.166 --> 00:15:59.583
Where were the marshmallows?

332
00:15:59.666 --> 00:16:03.375
I just saw them five seconds ago.
Where could they possibly go?

333
00:16:03.458 --> 00:16:05.416
One. two. three.

334
00:16:05.500 --> 00:16:07.750
They were just here.

335
00:16:07.833 --> 00:16:09.000
What are you doing?

336
00:16:09.083 --> 00:16:10.625
Keeping our family tradition alive.

337
00:16:10.708 --> 00:16:13.541
I'm trying to have a normal
Thanksgiving right now. okay?

338
00:16:13.625 --> 00:16:15.916
What's normal? Turkey. pumpkin pie?

339
00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:17.166
Boo. boring.

340
00:16:17.250 --> 00:16:19.458
Say what you will about Mom.
we always had fun.

341
00:16:19.541 --> 00:16:22.416
Okay. you have a very interesting.
selective memory.

342
00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:25.041
Can't we just enjoy this. please?

343
00:16:25.125 --> 00:16:27.333
You are ruining Tuck's Thanksgiving.

344
00:16:27.416 --> 00:16:30.125
[Tucker] They were just here.
The marshmallows were just here.

345
00:16:30.208 --> 00:16:32.250
Party people!

346
00:16:32.333 --> 00:16:34.000
-Happy Thanksgiving!
-Oh! Birdie!

347
00:16:34.083 --> 00:16:35.500
Nats! Thank God!

348
00:16:35.583 --> 00:16:38.833
-I thought we'd have too much food.
-Not a chance. We brought friends.

349
00:16:38.916 --> 00:16:40.250
And we brought wine.

350
00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:42.708
Oh. six. Six more people.
Hi. Kendall. Great.

351
00:16:42.791 --> 00:16:45.166
That's perfect. I can do that. Yeah.
Hi. how you doing?

352
00:16:45.250 --> 00:16:46.583
-Hi. Hi.
-Hi. Tucker. Thanks for having us.

353
00:16:46.666 --> 00:16:50.333
-[indistinct chatter]
-Good to see you.

354
00:16:50.416 --> 00:16:53.166
Is it possible to double a sweet potato
casserole in one dish?

355
00:16:53.250 --> 00:16:54.791
You're asking me?

356
00:16:55.291 --> 00:16:56.333
I got this.

357
00:16:57.291 --> 00:16:58.708
This is a bad idea.

358
00:16:58.791 --> 00:17:00.333
[Hannah] Yeah. you're right.

359
00:17:00.416 --> 00:17:02.333
Who brings a key lime pie to Thanksgiving?

360
00:17:02.416 --> 00:17:04.208
Why didn't you stop me? Pumpkin?

361
00:17:04.291 --> 00:17:06.541
Pumpkin is the thing.

362
00:17:06.625 --> 00:17:08.125
Or maybe I should have brought wine.

363
00:17:08.208 --> 00:17:10.000
I meant my dad. Wellsy.

364
00:17:10.666 --> 00:17:12.625
-Oh. right.
-[both laugh]

365
00:17:13.541 --> 00:17:16.000
And we can go at any point.

366
00:17:16.083 --> 00:17:18.041
Just give me the signal.
and we'll get the fuck out.

367
00:17:18.125 --> 00:17:19.833
-The signal?
-Yeah.

368
00:17:19.916 --> 00:17:22.375
Like. I don't know.
squeeze my hand or something.

369
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:23.791
Once means you're good.

370
00:17:23.875 --> 00:17:25.750
Two squeezes. and we're gone.

371
00:17:25.833 --> 00:17:27.291
[laughs]

372
00:17:28.916 --> 00:17:30.083
[sighs]

373
00:17:30.166 --> 00:17:31.875
Or we go?

374
00:17:36.375 --> 00:17:39.416
Or... Or we stay?
You gotta give me something here.

375
00:17:39.500 --> 00:17:40.541
[laughs]

376
00:17:40.625 --> 00:17:42.666
All right. we stay.

377
00:17:42.750 --> 00:17:43.708
Okay.

378
00:17:45.750 --> 00:17:48.166
First step. getting out the car.

379
00:17:48.250 --> 00:17:50.416
-[laughs]
-Yeah.

380
00:17:50.500 --> 00:17:51.875
[doorbell rings]

381
00:17:53.416 --> 00:17:55.208
Garrett. you made it.

382
00:17:55.291 --> 00:17:56.291
Dad.

383
00:17:56.375 --> 00:17:57.750
And you must be Hannah.

384
00:17:57.833 --> 00:17:59.583
-Glad to finally meet you.
-Hi.

385
00:17:59.666 --> 00:18:01.708
Sorry. I'd shake your hand. but--

386
00:18:01.791 --> 00:18:02.916
Oh. I'll take that.

387
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:04.125
Pie!

388
00:18:04.750 --> 00:18:07.541
Oh. it's key lime.
You love key lime.

389
00:18:07.625 --> 00:18:10.291
-He loves key lime.
-I do. it's the superior pie. thank you.

390
00:18:10.375 --> 00:18:12.625
Well. don't let the poor kids
freeze out there.

391
00:18:12.708 --> 00:18:13.750
Come in.

392
00:18:14.416 --> 00:18:16.500
I'm gonna put this in the fridge.

393
00:18:16.583 --> 00:18:17.958
I'll take your coats.

394
00:18:18.041 --> 00:18:19.250
Thank you.

395
00:18:20.958 --> 00:18:22.333
Thanks.

396
00:18:24.166 --> 00:18:25.500
[Hannah sighs]

397
00:18:25.583 --> 00:18:27.500
It's a nice house.

398
00:18:27.583 --> 00:18:29.208
-Yeah.
-[laughs]

399
00:18:30.458 --> 00:18:33.083
Aw! Look at you.

400
00:18:36.083 --> 00:18:37.041
Oh.

401
00:18:42.166 --> 00:18:44.250
They look alike. don't they?

402
00:18:44.333 --> 00:18:46.666
It's uncanny.

403
00:18:46.750 --> 00:18:48.625
I'm so glad you're here. Garrett.

404
00:18:48.708 --> 00:18:50.958
I can't wait to hear
all about how the season's going.

405
00:18:51.041 --> 00:18:52.291
[laughs]

406
00:18:52.375 --> 00:18:54.000
Come on. I'll put the game on.

407
00:18:54.083 --> 00:18:55.291
It's you versus me. kid.

408
00:18:55.375 --> 00:18:56.541
Rangers. Bruins.

409
00:18:56.625 --> 00:19:00.041
Actually. is it cool
if I show Hannah around first?

410
00:19:00.125 --> 00:19:01.833
Yeah. of course.

411
00:19:01.916 --> 00:19:04.250
You don't have to ask permission.
This is your house. too.

412
00:19:07.166 --> 00:19:08.125
Here. I'll give you the tour.

413
00:19:08.208 --> 00:19:09.666
Cool.

414
00:19:09.750 --> 00:19:10.625
[knock on door]

415
00:19:10.708 --> 00:19:12.250
Thank you so much.
Thank you for coming.

416
00:19:12.333 --> 00:19:13.958
Who is that now?

417
00:19:15.208 --> 00:19:16.708
We come bearing alcohol.

418
00:19:16.791 --> 00:19:20.583
And we got tiny little boxes of cereal
stolen from the dining hall.

419
00:19:20.666 --> 00:19:22.541
Hey. look. Tuck. More people.

420
00:19:22.625 --> 00:19:24.541
Hannah said orphans were welcome.

421
00:19:24.625 --> 00:19:26.416
They are. They are. yes.

422
00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:28.541
Uh. just grab a seat.

423
00:19:28.625 --> 00:19:30.000
Jules will grab you a drink.

424
00:19:31.375 --> 00:19:35.625
Yeah. Just make yourselves at home
here in the living room.

425
00:19:35.708 --> 00:19:37.791
Okay. thank you. guys. Happy Thanksgiving.

426
00:19:37.875 --> 00:19:39.375
[all] Happy Thanksgiving.

427
00:19:43.666 --> 00:19:45.166
[stove beeps]

428
00:19:45.250 --> 00:19:47.208
Why is the stuffing not in the oven yet?

429
00:19:47.291 --> 00:19:50.291
Because the corn pudding and the green
bean casserole are already in there.

430
00:19:50.375 --> 00:19:52.250
Here. please consult the oven schedule.

431
00:19:53.250 --> 00:19:54.541
I did all the math.

432
00:19:54.625 --> 00:19:57.541
The stuffing needs to hang out
in the neutral zone.

433
00:19:57.625 --> 00:19:59.416
-It only takes 30 minutes.
-[stove beeps]

434
00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:01.208
If you guys were half as good at hockey...

435
00:20:01.291 --> 00:20:03.291
Jules. I can't right now.

436
00:20:03.375 --> 00:20:04.291
Please.

437
00:20:04.375 --> 00:20:05.916
-Go.
-Gravy. Guys. please.

438
00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:07.666
-Somebody taste it. Thank you.
-Logan. try it.

439
00:20:09.416 --> 00:20:12.833
And for the end of the tour. this is me.

440
00:20:21.875 --> 00:20:22.833
You okay?

441
00:20:23.791 --> 00:20:26.083
Yeah. yeah. it's just weird
being back here.

442
00:20:26.166 --> 00:20:28.416
After my mom died.
I went off to boarding school.

443
00:20:28.500 --> 00:20:30.875
and I never really lived here again.

444
00:20:30.958 --> 00:20:33.041
Yeah. I can tell. [laughs]

445
00:20:33.125 --> 00:20:35.875
Is your dad running
a storage business on the side?

446
00:20:35.958 --> 00:20:37.250
[both chuckle]

447
00:20:37.916 --> 00:20:40.541
This is just all the stuff he signs
when he goes to mall appearances

448
00:20:40.625 --> 00:20:41.875
or conventions or whatever.

449
00:20:41.958 --> 00:20:42.916
Right.

450
00:20:43.541 --> 00:20:45.333
Trying to keep the legend alive.

451
00:20:46.750 --> 00:20:48.750
His best years are behind him.

452
00:20:51.291 --> 00:20:53.000
Are you afraid that'll happen to you?

453
00:20:53.083 --> 00:20:56.208
This is what success
looks like. eventually.

454
00:20:57.541 --> 00:20:59.416
Or I could tear my ACL tomorrow

455
00:20:59.500 --> 00:21:03.666
and get stuck bagging groceries
at the Stop 'N' Shop.

456
00:21:04.958 --> 00:21:07.375
Not that--
Not that there's anything wrong with that.

457
00:21:07.458 --> 00:21:10.416
Hey. my mom works at Bob's Market. so...

458
00:21:11.416 --> 00:21:14.375
Yeah. not-- Yeah. that wasn't really
a dream. either. so...

459
00:21:15.708 --> 00:21:17.291
What was?

460
00:21:17.375 --> 00:21:19.791
I don't know. She-- She was a singer.

461
00:21:19.875 --> 00:21:22.208
Her high school choir
won a bunch of competitions.

462
00:21:22.291 --> 00:21:24.250
but I don't know.
she never really went for it.

463
00:21:24.333 --> 00:21:26.083
She must be proud of you. then.

464
00:21:26.166 --> 00:21:28.708
Yeah. I just think
she wants me to be happy.

465
00:21:30.375 --> 00:21:32.916
My dad. he's not really like that.

466
00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:36.083
Or. I don't know about now. but he wasn't.

467
00:21:36.166 --> 00:21:38.625
Not just with hockey. with everything.
He was always...

468
00:21:39.958 --> 00:21:41.250
so...

469
00:21:41.333 --> 00:21:42.708
Intense?

470
00:21:42.791 --> 00:21:43.833
Yeah.

471
00:21:43.916 --> 00:21:46.041
-Yeah.
-Yeah. seriously intense.

472
00:21:55.208 --> 00:21:58.500
Yeah. I don't know.
it just seems kind of sad.

473
00:21:58.583 --> 00:22:01.875
Like you wake up one morning
and can't play hockey anymore.

474
00:22:01.958 --> 00:22:03.375
Would you miss it?

475
00:22:03.458 --> 00:22:05.125
It's the only thing I'm good at.

476
00:22:05.208 --> 00:22:07.541
That's not true. And that's not an answer.

477
00:22:07.625 --> 00:22:08.958
[laughs]

478
00:22:10.166 --> 00:22:11.583
I think I would be...

479
00:22:12.958 --> 00:22:14.833
like. relieved.

480
00:22:21.000 --> 00:22:22.250
[cell phone vibrates]

481
00:22:22.333 --> 00:22:23.416
Sorry.

482
00:22:24.958 --> 00:22:28.541
Uh. Allie said that they wanted
to wish me a Happy Thanksgiving.

483
00:22:28.625 --> 00:22:29.875
Take it.

484
00:22:29.958 --> 00:22:30.833
Are you sure?

485
00:22:36.416 --> 00:22:37.833
Yeah. I've got this.

486
00:22:39.166 --> 00:22:40.375
Okay.

487
00:22:43.625 --> 00:22:44.500
Hey.

488
00:22:44.583 --> 00:22:45.791
[laughing] Oh. my gosh!

489
00:22:45.875 --> 00:22:47.416
Hi. everyone.

490
00:22:50.500 --> 00:22:54.333
Okay. we have more people here
than a Walmart on a Black Friday.

491
00:22:54.416 --> 00:22:57.000
We are going to loaves and fishes
this whole thing.

492
00:22:57.083 --> 00:23:01.291
I'mma go get potatoes
from the extra fridge. and then. um...

493
00:23:01.375 --> 00:23:03.250
-Pat-dry?
-...pat-dry the bird. yes.

494
00:23:03.333 --> 00:23:05.083
-Yes.
-Go get 'em. buddy.

495
00:23:05.166 --> 00:23:07.875
Wait. wait. wait.
No marshmallows on the sweet potatoes?

496
00:23:07.958 --> 00:23:09.625
[man] They're already sweet.

497
00:23:09.708 --> 00:23:12.375
Okay. that's fucking blasphemy.
You're a blasphemer.

498
00:23:12.458 --> 00:23:13.791
I will die on this hill.

499
00:23:13.875 --> 00:23:16.125
We never had marshmallows
on our sweet potatoes.

500
00:23:16.208 --> 00:23:18.875
-We never had sweet potatoes.
-I had a sweet potato taco one year.

501
00:23:18.958 --> 00:23:21.291
Tacos? On Thanksgiving?

502
00:23:21.375 --> 00:23:23.333
It's actually the best time
for tacos. honestly.

503
00:23:23.833 --> 00:23:26.666
Especially when your big bro has a sweet
sponsorship deal with Taco Shack.

504
00:23:26.750 --> 00:23:29.041
Ah. They're open on Thanksgiving?

505
00:23:29.125 --> 00:23:31.416
Yeah. they're the only place
open on Thanksgiving.

506
00:23:31.500 --> 00:23:34.708
And we learned that the hard way
when our mom got drunk one year

507
00:23:34.791 --> 00:23:36.083
and forgot she was grilling chicken.

508
00:23:36.166 --> 00:23:38.208
The propane tank almost leveled the block.

509
00:23:38.291 --> 00:23:40.166
-Whoa.
-It was a blessing. actually.

510
00:23:40.250 --> 00:23:42.666
Mama Logan was never known
for her cooking.

511
00:23:43.916 --> 00:23:45.166
I know.

512
00:23:45.666 --> 00:23:47.000
We should bring Mom Taco Shack.

513
00:23:47.083 --> 00:23:48.541
Absolutely not.

514
00:23:49.416 --> 00:23:51.041
Well. she's probably surrounded
by strangers

515
00:23:51.125 --> 00:23:52.541
eating gross rehab food right now.

516
00:23:53.458 --> 00:23:54.458
So?

517
00:23:54.541 --> 00:23:56.666
So. she needs our support.

518
00:23:56.750 --> 00:23:57.833
Should we be here for this?

519
00:23:57.916 --> 00:24:01.041
I supported her the last time she went in.
and the time before that.

520
00:24:01.125 --> 00:24:02.000
and the time before that.

521
00:24:02.083 --> 00:24:04.000
It's Thanksgiving.
and she's fucking family. John.

522
00:24:04.083 --> 00:24:05.708
She's in fucking rehab. Jules.

523
00:24:05.791 --> 00:24:06.958
Exactly.

524
00:24:08.041 --> 00:24:09.541
She's...

525
00:24:09.625 --> 00:24:10.875
She's trying.

526
00:24:10.958 --> 00:24:14.500
Okay. new plan.
I'm gonna whip up some spinach casserole.

527
00:24:15.833 --> 00:24:16.875
What?

528
00:24:17.375 --> 00:24:18.583
You know what? Forget it.

529
00:24:19.083 --> 00:24:20.500
I'll go myself.

530
00:24:25.625 --> 00:24:27.458
Tucker! My friend.

531
00:24:27.541 --> 00:24:28.916
We are here.

532
00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:31.000
Yes. Yes. you are.

533
00:24:31.083 --> 00:24:32.541
I'm so sorry to be late.

534
00:24:32.625 --> 00:24:33.500
Uh-huh.

535
00:24:33.583 --> 00:24:35.500
-So. Yanis from Latvia.
-Hi.

536
00:24:36.000 --> 00:24:38.750
-Uh. Cheryl from Philippines.
-Hi.

537
00:24:38.833 --> 00:24:40.666
-You know Arjun?
-Mm-mm. Hi.

538
00:24:40.750 --> 00:24:43.125
-And Karl Heinz.
-Hello! Karl Heinz.

539
00:24:43.208 --> 00:24:44.250
[all laugh]

540
00:24:44.333 --> 00:24:46.375
-[glass shatters]
-[Lexi] Sorry.

541
00:24:47.208 --> 00:24:50.000
You know what. boys and girls?
I need space to work.

542
00:24:50.083 --> 00:24:52.708
Everybody. we are going
to take this shindig outside.

543
00:24:52.791 --> 00:24:54.916
Let's go. Outside. Outside. guys.

544
00:24:55.000 --> 00:24:56.833
-Outside. guys.
-[man] Outside.

545
00:24:56.916 --> 00:24:58.458
Thank you. guys.

546
00:24:58.541 --> 00:25:00.458
-[indistinct chatter]
-Thank you. guys.

547
00:25:02.708 --> 00:25:04.791
[exhales]

548
00:25:04.875 --> 00:25:06.500
[TV announcer] <i>The Bruins started the day</i>

549
00:25:06.583 --> 00:25:09.375
<i>three points clear</i>
<i>of fifth-place Philadelphia.</i>

550
00:25:09.458 --> 00:25:11.625
<i>and fourth in the East.</i>

551
00:25:11.708 --> 00:25:13.000
<i>The game is on.</i>

552
00:25:14.916 --> 00:25:18.541
<i>It looked like the Bruins</i>
<i>are gonna get that puck out.</i>

553
00:25:18.625 --> 00:25:21.041
I heard you stopped by
and saw a Bruins practice.

554
00:25:21.125 --> 00:25:22.666
Yeah.

555
00:25:22.750 --> 00:25:24.541
You get a chance to show off?

556
00:25:25.041 --> 00:25:26.708
Yeah. a little bit.

557
00:25:26.791 --> 00:25:28.041
Attaboy.

558
00:25:32.458 --> 00:25:35.541
Cindy seems... nice.

559
00:25:35.625 --> 00:25:36.583
She is.

560
00:25:36.666 --> 00:25:38.166
Knows hockey. too.

561
00:25:38.250 --> 00:25:40.416
Penguins fan. but we're working on that.

562
00:25:40.500 --> 00:25:41.916
All right. Good.

563
00:25:42.875 --> 00:25:44.583
-[cheering on TV]
-Mm!

564
00:25:44.666 --> 00:25:46.208
-There you go.
-Fuckin' A.

565
00:25:46.291 --> 00:25:47.458
There you go.

566
00:25:47.541 --> 00:25:49.791
Bonneville is giving the Bruins trouble.

567
00:25:49.875 --> 00:25:51.083
He's too fast for the D.

568
00:25:51.166 --> 00:25:52.708
Yeah. but he's slow on the backtrack.

569
00:25:52.791 --> 00:25:54.500
They've just got to get
the puck off him first.

570
00:25:54.583 --> 00:25:59.125
Mm. I bet the Bruins would love having you
on the ice a year early. huh?

571
00:25:59.208 --> 00:26:03.041
They don't need me yet.
Fontano's got a few seasons left in him.

572
00:26:03.125 --> 00:26:05.500
Plus. I'm not ready yet.

573
00:26:05.583 --> 00:26:06.791
I want to graduate.

574
00:26:06.875 --> 00:26:09.375
[announcer] <i>We'll be right back</i>
<i>after this commercial break.</i>

575
00:26:10.666 --> 00:26:12.875
That's a smart choice. Garrett.

576
00:26:14.833 --> 00:26:17.958
Probably good to be a little bit older
before you go pro.

577
00:26:18.833 --> 00:26:23.500
Eighteen was really young for me
to be thrown in the deep end.

578
00:26:23.583 --> 00:26:25.666
You'll be better equipped
to handle the pressure.

579
00:26:29.125 --> 00:26:30.791
[announcer]
<i>And we're back.</i>

580
00:26:30.875 --> 00:26:33.916
<i>Face off won by Levy</i>
<i>and the Bruins set it up.</i>

581
00:26:34.000 --> 00:26:36.416
<i>The Rangers' penalty killing</i>
<i>has been outstanding.</i>

582
00:26:36.500 --> 00:26:39.458
<i>A huge factor in the game</i>
<i>against the Bruins today.</i>

583
00:26:39.541 --> 00:26:40.833
Okay. are you alone now?

584
00:26:40.916 --> 00:26:43.000
Can we talk about Aunt Kathy's
new British accent?

585
00:26:43.083 --> 00:26:45.666
And she goes by Kiara now.

586
00:26:45.750 --> 00:26:47.375
It's like a whole thing.

587
00:26:47.458 --> 00:26:49.333
Wasn't she in London for. like. a week?

588
00:26:49.416 --> 00:26:51.041
-[boisterous chatter]
-[cell phone vibrating]

589
00:26:52.041 --> 00:26:54.000
<i>-Al?</i>
-Huh?

590
00:26:54.083 --> 00:26:56.208
<i>Um. no. yeah. totally.</i>

591
00:26:56.291 --> 00:26:59.291
Uh. okay. what-- What's going on?

592
00:26:59.375 --> 00:27:02.000
<i>Nothing. it's just like everyone's over.</i>

593
00:27:02.083 --> 00:27:03.666
Hey. if you're busy. I...

594
00:27:03.750 --> 00:27:06.541
Hey. Allie Hayes. I can hear your nails.
Who are you texting?

595
00:27:06.625 --> 00:27:08.500
What? Nobody.

596
00:27:08.583 --> 00:27:09.833
It's Sean.

597
00:27:09.916 --> 00:27:11.875
-You're backsliding.
-Am not.

598
00:27:12.791 --> 00:27:14.291
Hey. it's okay.

599
00:27:14.375 --> 00:27:15.458
[laughs]

600
00:27:15.541 --> 00:27:17.000
It's my dad. He. uh...

601
00:27:18.000 --> 00:27:19.958
He can't find the remote again. He--

602
00:27:20.041 --> 00:27:22.958
I swear he has ADHD.
but his generation's undiagnosable.

603
00:27:24.166 --> 00:27:25.458
Oh. okay.

604
00:27:26.458 --> 00:27:28.458
Hey. I should probably go help.

605
00:27:28.541 --> 00:27:30.625
Um. love you. miss you. Gobble. gobble.

606
00:27:30.708 --> 00:27:32.083
-[call disconnects]
-Oh...

607
00:27:38.416 --> 00:27:39.791
[sighs]

608
00:27:56.583 --> 00:27:57.833
[chuckles]

609
00:28:39.833 --> 00:28:41.125
Happy Thanksgiving.

610
00:28:41.208 --> 00:28:42.791
-You have an appointment?
-Hi.

611
00:28:42.875 --> 00:28:44.916
No. I'm-- I'm here for Jean Logan.

612
00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:46.458
And when did she check in?

613
00:28:46.541 --> 00:28:47.625
Last week.

614
00:28:47.708 --> 00:28:50.916
I'm sorry. new intakes
don't have visitation privileges yet.

615
00:28:51.000 --> 00:28:53.291
No. I. uh... I have a delivery.

616
00:28:54.250 --> 00:28:56.333
Can you just tell her it's from Jules?

617
00:28:56.916 --> 00:28:57.958
[Logan] And John.

618
00:29:01.291 --> 00:29:02.416
Excuse me?

619
00:29:02.500 --> 00:29:04.833
I paid for this with my hard-earned cash.

620
00:29:04.916 --> 00:29:06.041
Well. I'll Venmo you.

621
00:29:06.125 --> 00:29:07.958
Jules and John. thank you.

622
00:29:08.041 --> 00:29:11.541
[receptionist] Any particular message?
"Happy Thanksgiving." or...

623
00:29:11.625 --> 00:29:14.041
Actually. uh. contraband. please.

624
00:29:25.208 --> 00:29:26.708
It's a family tradition.

625
00:29:27.958 --> 00:29:29.000
She'll get it.

626
00:29:31.500 --> 00:29:33.041
Thank you.

627
00:29:33.125 --> 00:29:34.500
It'll mean a lot to her.

628
00:29:35.041 --> 00:29:37.250
Well. I'm here
because it means a lot to you.

629
00:29:37.791 --> 00:29:39.125
And you're right.

630
00:29:40.375 --> 00:29:41.791
She is trying.

631
00:29:48.250 --> 00:29:51.916
So. what do you say we hit
the hardware store on the way back?

632
00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:53.125
For real?

633
00:29:53.208 --> 00:29:55.041
I mean. we gotta shore up our supplies

634
00:29:55.125 --> 00:29:57.458
if we're gonna spread
the Logan love this holiday season.

635
00:29:57.541 --> 00:30:01.041
In that case. we'd better hit
the Stop 'N' Shop. too.

636
00:30:01.125 --> 00:30:03.916
One bag of marshmallows
ain't gonna cut it.

637
00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:07.125
-[snaps fingers]
-Let's go. Come on.

638
00:30:07.208 --> 00:30:08.083
[timers beeping]

639
00:30:08.166 --> 00:30:11.583
<i>♪I'm your leader. I'm your teacher</i>
<i>I'm your Michelin Man...♪</i>

640
00:30:11.666 --> 00:30:14.000
-Status check.
-All sides in the oven. Chef.

641
00:30:14.083 --> 00:30:15.458
T-minus one hour. Chef.

642
00:30:15.541 --> 00:30:17.333
-I've always wanted to say that.
-We crushed it.

643
00:30:17.416 --> 00:30:21.625
Which means. <i>mis amigos.</i>
it is time to deep-fry the turkey!

644
00:30:21.708 --> 00:30:23.708
[all cheer]

645
00:30:24.208 --> 00:30:26.375
-Simms. you ready?
-Let's fucking do this.

646
00:30:26.458 --> 00:30:28.833
[all] Ten. nine. eight.

647
00:30:28.916 --> 00:30:31.833
seven. six. five.

648
00:30:31.916 --> 00:30:36.083
four. three. two.

649
00:30:36.166 --> 00:30:37.708
one!

650
00:30:37.791 --> 00:30:40.208
Wait. I forgot to pat-dry the bird!

651
00:30:40.291 --> 00:30:41.333
Oh!

652
00:30:41.416 --> 00:30:43.375
["National Treasure"
by Barns Courtney playing]

653
00:31:04.458 --> 00:31:07.375
-[man] Bonfire party!
-[cheering]

654
00:31:09.916 --> 00:31:11.916
[mellow dinner music playing]

655
00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:14.125
You guys are in for quite a treat.

656
00:31:14.208 --> 00:31:17.000
Cindy's mashed potatoes
are really something.

657
00:31:17.083 --> 00:31:18.458
And dairy-free.

658
00:31:18.541 --> 00:31:20.083
It's a happy accident. Hannah.

659
00:31:21.958 --> 00:31:24.750
I asked Cindy to. uh.

660
00:31:24.833 --> 00:31:26.583
make the mac and cheese...

661
00:31:27.250 --> 00:31:29.583
-With the breadcrumbs. uh-huh.
-With the breadcrumbs.

662
00:31:29.666 --> 00:31:31.416
-Like Mom used to make.
-[Phil] Mm-hmm.

663
00:31:32.000 --> 00:31:33.333
I didn't want to overstep.

664
00:31:33.416 --> 00:31:35.166
[Garrett] No.

665
00:31:35.250 --> 00:31:37.708
No. that's-- that's very kind. Thank you.

666
00:31:37.791 --> 00:31:39.083
[Phil] Thanks for coming.

667
00:31:40.666 --> 00:31:42.125
It means a lot to me.

668
00:31:46.500 --> 00:31:48.333
Phil. would you?

669
00:31:48.416 --> 00:31:49.708
Yes. of course.

670
00:31:49.791 --> 00:31:52.000
We should say a little grace
before we dig in.

671
00:31:53.000 --> 00:31:54.750
Oh.

672
00:31:54.833 --> 00:31:56.000
Yeah.

673
00:31:58.833 --> 00:32:03.958
Lord. thank you for this wonderful bounty
you have bestowed upon us.

674
00:32:04.958 --> 00:32:09.000
Thank you for bringing us all together
to enjoy this delicious meal.

675
00:32:09.083 --> 00:32:11.041
And for the hands that prepared it.

676
00:32:12.416 --> 00:32:15.041
We ask you to guide us

677
00:32:15.125 --> 00:32:18.541
towards love and understanding.

678
00:32:21.958 --> 00:32:26.000
[voice becoming muffled] To experience
what it means to be family.

679
00:32:29.750 --> 00:32:32.416
<i>In this life and the next.</i>

680
00:32:32.500 --> 00:32:33.583
[angry shouting]

681
00:32:33.666 --> 00:32:35.041
<i>Thank you. Lord.</i>

682
00:32:36.083 --> 00:32:38.083
[muffled thuds]

683
00:32:40.083 --> 00:32:41.416
[normal audio resumes] Amen.

684
00:32:43.833 --> 00:32:45.125
Amen.

685
00:32:58.916 --> 00:33:00.666
Everything okay?

686
00:33:00.750 --> 00:33:01.625
[Cindy] Yeah.

687
00:33:01.708 --> 00:33:03.208
I just got a chill.

688
00:33:03.291 --> 00:33:05.000
She's thin-skinned. this one.

689
00:33:05.083 --> 00:33:07.708
Not built for Boston winter.

690
00:33:07.791 --> 00:33:11.208
Why don't you go upstairs
and get a different sweater. darling?

691
00:33:14.208 --> 00:33:15.416
No! Don't!

692
00:33:15.500 --> 00:33:18.083
-Whoa!
-Just sit.

693
00:33:19.625 --> 00:33:21.291
Is there a problem?

694
00:33:22.333 --> 00:33:23.583
Sorry. I just...

695
00:33:25.750 --> 00:33:27.125
I need a...

696
00:33:27.208 --> 00:33:28.250
Um...

697
00:33:28.333 --> 00:33:29.708
I'm so sorry.

698
00:33:29.791 --> 00:33:31.791
I'm not feeling well.

699
00:33:35.708 --> 00:33:36.750
Can we go?

700
00:33:40.333 --> 00:33:41.541
Let's go.

701
00:33:43.875 --> 00:33:45.833
-[breathing heavily]
-Slow down.

702
00:33:46.500 --> 00:33:48.541
-Garrett. give me the keys. I'm driving.
-Hannah.

703
00:33:48.625 --> 00:33:49.666
Garrett.

704
00:33:50.875 --> 00:33:52.375
Please.

705
00:33:53.750 --> 00:33:56.333
Wait! Your coats!

706
00:33:58.291 --> 00:33:59.375
Thank you.

707
00:34:00.958 --> 00:34:02.916
I'm gonna go warm up the car.

708
00:34:08.333 --> 00:34:09.375
Your wrist.

709
00:34:09.458 --> 00:34:10.833
It was an accident.

710
00:34:10.916 --> 00:34:12.166
No. it wasn't.

711
00:34:12.833 --> 00:34:14.500
I'm sorry I ruined Thanksgiving.

712
00:34:14.583 --> 00:34:16.333
Your father really wanted us all to...

713
00:34:16.416 --> 00:34:18.708
No. you-you-you didn't ruin...

714
00:34:21.041 --> 00:34:23.291
You can't stay with him.

715
00:34:23.375 --> 00:34:25.791
Look. he felt awful after.

716
00:34:25.875 --> 00:34:27.250
And it's just...

717
00:34:27.333 --> 00:34:29.875
-It's not who he is.
-It's exactly who he is.

718
00:34:29.958 --> 00:34:32.583
He says it's not
gonna happen again. right?

719
00:34:32.666 --> 00:34:35.750
He makes promises. He says he'll change.
It's a lie. It's all a fucking lie.

720
00:34:35.833 --> 00:34:37.666
He doesn't care about you.
He doesn't care about me.

721
00:34:37.750 --> 00:34:39.416
All he cares about is Phil fucking Graham.
That's it.

722
00:34:39.500 --> 00:34:41.250
Listen to me.

723
00:34:41.333 --> 00:34:43.500
My mom didn't have the chance to get out.

724
00:34:43.583 --> 00:34:44.958
But you do.

725
00:34:46.708 --> 00:34:48.041
Please leave.

726
00:34:48.125 --> 00:34:49.250
Please.

727
00:35:01.875 --> 00:35:03.541
It's complicated.

728
00:35:06.041 --> 00:35:06.958
[sighs]

729
00:35:07.041 --> 00:35:09.041
["Over and Over Again"
by Matthew Perryman Jones playing]

730
00:35:16.041 --> 00:35:17.291
-[door closes]
-[sighs]

731
00:35:18.333 --> 00:35:22.166
<i>♪I can see you in myself♪</i>

732
00:35:22.250 --> 00:35:25.875
<i>♪And it's scaring me to death♪</i>

733
00:35:26.875 --> 00:35:30.166
<i>♪You're running from what was♪</i>

734
00:35:30.250 --> 00:35:33.208
<i>♪And what hasn't happened yet♪</i>

735
00:35:34.375 --> 00:35:37.375
<i>♪I can't be someone else♪</i>

736
00:35:37.458 --> 00:35:41.500
<i>♪But I can't be like this♪</i>

737
00:35:41.583 --> 00:35:47.083
<i>♪Any longer♪</i>

738
00:35:47.166 --> 00:35:49.333
<i>♪Guess you give♪</i>

739
00:35:49.416 --> 00:35:53.083
<i>♪What you're given...♪</i>

740
00:35:53.166 --> 00:35:54.708
Garrett.

741
00:35:54.791 --> 00:35:55.958
Are you okay?

742
00:35:57.000 --> 00:35:59.416
Yeah. Yeah. I'm-- I'm fine.

743
00:36:01.000 --> 00:36:02.291
No. you're not.

744
00:36:02.375 --> 00:36:04.750
<i>♪And my heart♪</i>

745
00:36:04.833 --> 00:36:08.458
<i>♪Just gets broken♪</i>

746
00:36:08.541 --> 00:36:10.583
